"unit files and managed by systemd. Each container is a systemd service — "
"you can start, stop, restart, and enable autostart from the compartment "
"view."
msgstr ""

#: quadletman/templates/partials/help.html:27
msgid "Images can be pulled from a registry, referenced from a pre-pulled"
msgstr ""

#: quadletman/templates/partials/help.html:27
msgid "unit, or built from a Containerfile stored in the compartment."
msgstr ""

#: quadletman/templates/partials/help.html:34
msgid "Volumes and mounts"
msgstr ""

#: quadletman/templates/partials/help.html:40
msgid "Managed volumes"
msgstr ""

#: quadletman/templates/partials/help.html:41
msgid ""
"Created in the Volumes section of a compartment. quadletman allocates a "
"host directory and applies the correct SELinux label automatically."
msgstr ""

#: quadletman/templates/partials/help.html:43
msgid ""
"Once created, a volume is mounted into a container from the Volumes tab "
"of the container form. Each mount has an optional options field:"
msgstr ""

#: quadletman/templates/partials/help.html:45
msgid ""
"— Podman remaps file ownership to the container's primary user. Use when "
"the container runs as non-root and gets permission errors."
msgstr ""

#: quadletman/templates/partials/help.html:46
msgid ""
"— Same effect as U but using kernel ID-mapped mounts without modifying "
"files on disk. Requires kernel 5.12+ and Podman 4.1+."
msgstr ""

#: quadletman/templates/partials/help.html:47
msgid "— Mount read-only."
msgstr ""

#: quadletman/templates/partials/help.html:48
msgid "— Apply a private SELinux label (only needed when SELinux is enforcing)."
msgstr ""

#: quadletman/templates/partials/help.html:50
msgid "Options can be combined with commas, e.g."
msgstr ""

#: quadletman/templates/partials/help.html:55
msgid "Quadlet-managed volumes"
msgstr ""

#: quadletman/templates/partials/help.html:56
msgid ""
"An optional mode for managed volumes. Instead of a plain host directory, "
"quadletman generates a"
msgstr ""

#: quadletman/templates/partials/help.html:56
msgid ""
"unit file that Podman manages as a named volume. This enables advanced "
"storage options: a custom driver, a specific device, and driver-level "
"mount options."
msgstr ""

#: quadletman/templates/partials/help.html:57
msgid ""
"Enable the Quadlet volume toggle when creating a volume to use this mode."
" Leave it off for the simpler host-directory mode, which is sufficient "
"for most use cases."
msgstr ""

#: quadletman/templates/partials/help.html:62
msgid "Bind mounts"
msgstr ""

#: quadletman/templates/partials/help.html:63
msgid ""
"Mount any existing host path directly into a container — no volume needs "
"to be created first. Configured in the Volumes tab of the container form."
msgstr ""

#: quadletman/templates/partials/help.html:64
msgid ""
"Useful for exposing host configuration files, sockets, or device nodes. "
"The same options apply as for managed volume mounts."
msgstr ""

#: quadletman/templates/partials/help.html:65
msgid "Certain sensitive paths are blocked:"
msgstr ""

#: quadletman/templates/partials/help.html:65
msgid "and other system directories cannot be bind-mounted."
msgstr ""

#: quadletman/templates/partials/help.html:74
msgid "Helper users"
msgstr ""

#: quadletman/templates/partials/help.html:77
msgid ""
"Rootless Podman maps container UIDs to host UIDs via a user namespace. By"
" default, container UID 0 (root inside the container) maps to the "
"compartment's Linux user"
msgstr ""

#: quadletman/templates/partials/help.html:77
msgid ""
"and every other container UID maps to an unprivileged host UID drawn from"
" that user's subUID range."
msgstr ""

#: quadletman/templates/partials/help.html:78
msgid ""
"This works transparently for most containers, but causes a problem with "
"volume ownership: if a container process runs as UID 1000, the files it "
"writes to a volume are owned by the corresponding host subUID — a number "
"like 165536 that no named user owns. Browsing or backing up those files "
"from the host becomes awkward."
msgstr ""

#: quadletman/templates/partials/help.html:79
msgid ""
"Helper users solve this. When you add a UID mapping for container UID N, "
"quadletman creates a real Linux user"
msgstr ""

#: quadletman/templates/partials/help.html:79
msgid ""
"whose host UID is exactly the subUID that Podman maps container UID N to."
" You can then set a volume's owner to that helper user, and the volume "
"directory is owned by a named host account — no numeric UID hunting "
"required."
msgstr ""

#: quadletman/templates/partials/help.html:80
msgid ""
"Helper users are created and removed automatically by quadletman as you "
"add or remove UID mappings. They appear in the Helper Users section of a "
"compartment when at least one exists."
msgstr ""

#: quadletman/templates/partials/help.html:81
msgid ""
"All users belonging to a compartment — the compartment root and every "
"helper user — share a single Linux group named"
msgstr ""

